<script setup lang="ts">
defineProps<{kind:'letter'|'essay'}>()
type Sample={title:string;type:string;prompt:string;paragraphs:{label:string;text:string}[]}
const letters:Sample[]=[
{title:'酒店房间投诉信',type:'Formal',prompt:'You recently stayed at a hotel and were dissatisfied with your room. Describe the problems, explain how they affected you, and say what you would like the manager to do.',paragraphs:[
{label:'Greeting',text:'Dear Sir or Madam,'},{label:'Purpose',text:'I am writing to complain about the room I stayed in at your hotel from 8 to 10 July. I chose your hotel because of its good location and positive reviews, but unfortunately, the room did not meet a reasonable standard.'},{label:'Bullet 1',text:'The main problem was that the air conditioner did not work, even though the weather was extremely warm. In addition, the bathroom had not been cleaned properly, and there were no clean towels when I arrived. I reported these issues to reception, but no one came to help that evening.'},{label:'Bullet 2',text:'As a result, I was unable to sleep well and had to attend an important work meeting the next morning feeling tired. I also had to buy a towel from a nearby shop, which was both inconvenient and unnecessary.'},{label:'Bullet 3',text:'I would appreciate it if you could provide a partial refund for my stay and explain why the problems were not dealt with promptly. I also hope you will check the room before offering it to another guest.'},{label:'Closing',text:'I look forward to your response.\n\nYours faithfully,\nAlex Chen'}]},
{title:'向经理申请调班',type:'Semi-formal',prompt:'Write to your manager because you cannot work your usual shift. Explain why, suggest another arrangement, and say how you will complete your duties.',paragraphs:[
{label:'Greeting',text:'Dear Ms Brown,'},{label:'Purpose',text:'I am writing to ask whether I could change my shift next Saturday, 20 July. I understand that the store will be busy that weekend, so I wanted to contact you as early as possible.'},{label:'Bullet 1',text:'The reason for my request is that two close friends of mine are getting married that afternoon. My boyfriend and I have known them for several years, and we have already agreed to help them with a few things before the ceremony. Therefore, I will not be able to work my normal afternoon shift.'},{label:'Bullet 2',text:'I have spoken to Maria, and she is willing to take my Saturday shift. In return, I can work her full shift on Sunday. This arrangement would mean that the store still has the same number of employees on both days.'},{label:'Bullet 3',text:'Before leaving on Friday, I will finish the stock check and update the product list. I will also tell Maria about any customer orders that still need attention.'},{label:'Closing',text:'Thank you for considering my request. Please let me know if this arrangement is acceptable.\n\nKind regards,\nAlex'}]},
{title:'邀请朋友看演唱会',type:'Informal',prompt:'Write to a friend and invite them to a concert. Explain why they would enjoy it and give details about the arrangements.',paragraphs:[
{label:'Greeting',text:'Hi Amy,'},{label:'Purpose',text:"Hope you're doing well! I have some exciting news. My boyfriend and I are planning to see Joker Xue at Rogers Arena in downtown Vancouver, and we have an extra ticket. Would you like to come with us?"},{label:'Bullet 1',text:'The concert is on Saturday, 17 August, and it starts at 7:30 in the evening. We are planning to meet outside Stadium–Chinatown Station at around 6:15, so we will have plenty of time to walk to the arena and find our seats.'},{label:'Bullet 2',text:"I think you'd really enjoy the concert because you already know several of his songs. He is not only a good singer but also very funny when he talks to the audience. I saw him once before, and the atmosphere was amazing because everyone sang together."},{label:'Bullet 3',text:"After the concert, we're thinking of going to a barbecue restaurant nearby with a few friends. You can stay at my place that night, so you won't need to travel home late."},{label:'Closing',text:"Let me know if you can make it. I really hope you can join us!\n\nBest wishes,\nAlex"}]}
]
const essays:Sample[]=[
{title:'网购会取代实体店吗？',type:'Agree / Disagree',prompt:'Some people think that online shopping will eventually replace physical stores. To what extent do you agree or disagree?',paragraphs:[
{label:'Introduction',text:'Online shopping has become a normal part of daily life, and some people believe that it will cause all physical shops to disappear. I largely disagree with this view because customers still need to see certain products in person, and many people value the service and experience provided by real stores.'},{label:'Body 1',text:'The first reason is that some products are difficult to choose online. For example, customers often want to try clothes before buying them or test the colour of a beauty product on their skin. Pictures on a website may not show the exact size, quality or colour of an item. Although online stores usually allow returns, sending an unsuitable product back takes time and can be inconvenient. In a physical shop, customers can examine the product and make a more confident decision immediately.'},{label:'Body 2',text:'Another important reason is that shops offer personal service and a social experience. A trained employee can listen to a customer\'s needs, explain the differences between products and suggest a suitable choice. This is particularly useful for older customers or people buying an unfamiliar product. Shopping centres also contain restaurants, cinemas and other places where friends and families can spend time together. A website may be convenient, but it cannot completely provide this kind of human contact.'},{label:'Conclusion',text:'In conclusion, online shopping will continue to grow because it is fast and offers a wide range of products. However, I do not believe it will fully replace physical stores, since people still need to test some products and receive face-to-face service.'}]},
{title:'低价还是优质服务？',type:'Discuss Both Views',prompt:'Some people believe shops should focus on low prices, while others think good customer service is more important. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.',paragraphs:[
{label:'Introduction',text:'People have different views about whether shops should mainly provide low prices or high-quality customer service. Low prices clearly help customers save money, but I believe good service is more important for building a successful business in the long term.'},{label:'Body 1',text:'On the one hand, many customers choose a shop because its products are affordable. The cost of housing, food and transport has increased in many cities, so families need to control their spending. If two shops sell the same item, most people will probably choose the cheaper one. Low prices can also make useful products available to a larger number of people. For example, an affordable supermarket allows a family to buy enough food without using all of its weekly income. Therefore, price is an important part of a customer\'s decision.'},{label:'Body 2',text:'On the other hand, good customer service can create trust and encourage people to return. Employees who are patient and well trained can answer questions, solve problems and help customers select the right product. In a beauty store, for instance, a customer may need advice about which skincare product is suitable for dry or sensitive skin. A cheaper product is not useful if it is the wrong choice. In my view, customers are often willing to pay a little more when they feel respected and receive helpful advice.'},{label:'Conclusion',text:'In conclusion, low prices are important because they reduce pressure on customers. However, I believe good service has greater long-term value, as it helps customers make better choices and creates a positive relationship between a shop and the public.'}]},
{title:'网上购买美妆产品',type:'Advantages / Disadvantages',prompt:'More people are buying beauty products online. What are the advantages and disadvantages of this development?',paragraphs:[
{label:'Introduction',text:'Buying skincare and makeup products online has become increasingly common. This development offers greater convenience and choice, but it also creates problems because customers cannot always test a product or receive personal advice.'},{label:'Body 1',text:'One major advantage is that online shopping saves time. Customers can compare prices, read product information and place an order without travelling to several different shops. This is especially helpful for people who work long hours or live far from a large shopping centre. Online stores may also offer a wider range of brands and colours than a small local shop. In addition, customer reviews can provide useful information about the quality of a product. As a result, people can research many options before spending their money.'},{label:'Body 2',text:'However, there are also clear disadvantages. Colours can look different on a phone or computer screen, so a customer may order makeup that does not match their skin. It is also difficult to know whether a cream will feel comfortable or cause a reaction without trying it first. Furthermore, online information can be confusing, and some reviews may not be honest. In a physical beauty store, an employee can ask questions about the customer\'s needs and recommend a suitable product. Returning an unsuitable online order may take several days and create extra packaging waste.'},{label:'Conclusion',text:'In conclusion, buying beauty products online is convenient and gives customers more choice. Nevertheless, the inability to test products and receive face-to-face advice can lead to poor decisions. Customers should therefore check product details and return policies carefully before ordering.'}]},
{title:'城市交通拥堵',type:'Problems / Solutions',prompt:'Many cities suffer from traffic congestion. What problems does this cause, and what measures can be taken to solve them?',paragraphs:[
{label:'Introduction',text:'Traffic congestion is a serious issue in many growing cities. It wastes people\'s time and harms the environment, but governments can reduce these problems by improving public transport and making other forms of travel safer.'},{label:'Body 1',text:'The main problem caused by heavy traffic is the loss of time. Many workers spend a large part of each day sitting in their cars instead of working, resting or spending time with their families. Long and uncertain journeys can also increase stress, especially when people are worried about arriving late. Another problem is air pollution. When thousands of vehicles move slowly or remain still with their engines running, they produce harmful gases. This can reduce air quality and contribute to health problems, particularly for children and older people.'},{label:'Body 2',text:'One practical solution is for city governments to provide reliable and affordable public transport. Buses and trains need to be frequent, clean and connected to residential areas. If the service is convenient, more drivers may be willing to leave their cars at home. For example, a worker may choose a direct and reliable bus instead of driving alone to the city centre each morning. Cities should also build safe bicycle lanes and improve walking routes for shorter journeys. Finally, charging drivers to enter the busiest city areas during peak hours could reduce unnecessary car trips. The money collected could then be used to improve the transport system.'},{label:'Conclusion',text:'In conclusion, traffic congestion causes wasted time, stress and pollution. These effects can be reduced if governments offer better public transport, support cycling and walking, and discourage unnecessary driving in crowded areas.'}]},
{title:'频繁更换工作',type:'Two Questions',prompt:'More people now change jobs several times during their careers. Why is this the case? Is this a positive or negative development?',paragraphs:[
{label:'Introduction',text:'It is now common for people to work for several different employers during their careers. This mainly happens because workers want better opportunities and working conditions. In my view, it is generally a positive development, although changing jobs too frequently can create some uncertainty.'},{label:'Body 1',text:'The main reason people change jobs is that they want to improve their lives. A new position may offer a higher salary, more flexible hours or a better chance of promotion. Some workers also leave because they are no longer learning anything useful in their current role. Modern job websites make it easy to discover and apply for new opportunities. In addition, people are more willing than previous generations to move to another city or country for work. For example, a retail employee may move to a larger company in order to receive training and take on more responsibility.'},{label:'Body 2',text:'I believe this trend is mostly positive because workers can develop a wider range of skills and find jobs that suit them better. Working in different places can improve communication, confidence and the ability to deal with change. Employers may also improve pay and conditions when they know that good employees have other choices. However, moving too often may prevent a person from building strong professional relationships or completing long-term projects. For this reason, people should change jobs for a clear benefit rather than simply because a role becomes difficult.'},{label:'Conclusion',text:'In conclusion, people mainly change jobs to gain better pay, growth and flexibility. Overall, this is a positive development because it gives workers more control over their careers, provided that their decisions are carefully considered.'}]}
]
function words(paragraphs:Sample['paragraphs']){return paragraphs.reduce((n,p)=>n+p.text.trim().split(/\s+/).length,0)}
</script>
<template><section class="sample-section"><div class="guide-head"><el-tag type="success">COMPLETE ANSWERS</el-tag><h2>{{kind==='letter'?'三封 G 类书信完整范文':'五篇 G 类大作文完整范文'}}</h2><p>先看题目和段落标签，再完整阅读。范文目标是任务覆盖、逻辑和准确性，不是难词数量。</p></div><el-collapse accordion><el-collapse-item v-for="(sample,i) in kind==='letter'?letters:essays" :key="sample.title" :name="i"><template #title><span class="sample-title"><el-tag size="small">{{sample.type}}</el-tag><b>{{sample.title}}</b><small>{{words(sample.paragraphs)}} words</small></span></template><div class="sample-prompt"><b>Question</b><p>{{sample.prompt}}</p></div><div class="sample-answer"><div v-for="p in sample.paragraphs" :key="p.label"><span>{{p.label}}</span><p v-for="line in p.text.split('\n')" :key="line">{{line||'\u00a0'}}</p></div></div></el-collapse-item></el-collapse></section></template>
